#X text 528 93 The [fbdelay2~] object that was briefly presented earlier has the same structure as the feedback loop presented in this patch. Hence \, it is well suited for implementing a Flanger. Since it doesn't require a subpatch with a block size of 1 \, it is more efficient. Check the help file for more details., f 45;
#X obj 642 453 fbdelay2~ 50;
#X text 46 32 A flanger with feedback builds upon the feedforward delay structure and adds a feedback loop. The feedback parameter in delays is also known as "regeneration". Note that negative values are allowed., f 61;
#X text 46 97 Below we use Vanilla's [delwrite~] and [delread4~] objects in a subpatch with block size of 1 so we can have very short delay lines. As for the LFO \, we now have and amplitude width and a minimum delay. And instead of a dry/wet knob we have a depth parameter that mixes the output of the delay to the original. This is a more formal/classic implementation of a flanger. Open the [pd feedback-flanger] subpatch for more details., f 61;
